Schema Audit — Demo Day Room
The schema from CLAUDE.md for reference:

🔴 Structural Breaks — Wrong data or lost data at runtime
1. project_briefs and hackathon_briefs have no is_active or created_at

The brief re-submission flow (FR-BRIEF-06, NFR-BRIEF-03) creates new rows on each submit and marks old ones status = 'superseded'. But there is no is_active flag and no created_at timestamp on either table.

The Debrief agent's MCP tool get_project_brief must return the "current" brief. Without is_active or a timestamp, the query is ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 1 — but created_at doesn't exist. The tool has no deterministic way to find the right row.

Fix:

2. qa_turns uses a plain INDEX, not UNIQUE INDEX

The schema comment shows -- INDEX (qa_session_id, sequence_number). But sequence_number is client-incremented and turn writes are fire-and-forget with 3 retries. If the original request was slow (not failed) and a retry also succeeds, you get two rows with sequence_number = 5 for the same qa_session_id.

The Debrief agent reads all turns IN ORDER to generate the fracture map. Duplicate turns = doubled evidence = skewed scores.

Fix:

3. debriefs has no FK to qa_sessions

The Debrief agent's MCP tool get_qa_turns takes session_id — but a session can have multiple qa_sessions (started, abandoned via Cloud Scheduler → status = 'abandoned', started again). When the MCP tool queries turns for a session, it must decide which qa_session to use.

There is no FK on debriefs pointing to which qa_session was used to generate it. This means:

The MCP tool must guess (probably "latest non-abandoned qa_session")
If the founder abandoned Q&A and started again, the debrief may pull turns from the abandoned session
Fix:

Set this when creating the debriefs record at stream-start time. The agent then knows exactly which turns to read.

4. coach_messages has no FK to debriefs

The Coach conversation is grounded in a specific debrief. The founder can re-run the debrief (FR-DEBRIEF-09), creating a new debriefs record with attempt_number = 2. Old coach messages stay linked to session_id only.

When the coach sub-view reopens after a re-run debrief:

It loads all coach_messages for the session (including old ones from debrief v1)
But get_debrief_output MCP tool returns debrief v2 (the new is_active = true record)
The coach now has a conversation history that references things from v1 but tool output from v2
The agent will either contradict itself or confuse the founder by mixing evidence from two different debriefs.

Fix:

When the coach session starts, record which debriefs.id is active. Load only messages for that debrief_id. Start a fresh coach conversation after a re-run.

5. pitch_recordings missing mime_type column

The STT pipeline Cloud Task reads the video file from GCS and calls Speech-to-Text v2. The STT API requires an encoding parameter (WEBM_OPUS, MP4, etc.). The encoding is determined by which browser recorded the pitch.

The mime_type is known at record creation time (from MediaRecorder.mimeType), but there's no column to store it. The Cloud Task worker has no way to recover it later — it would need to sniff the file format from GCS, which is fragile.

Fix:

6. sessions.title has no defined write path

The column exists. The SessionCard displays it as a title. But no API route, Cloud Task, or trigger is documented to write it. The Brief Extraction Agent writes to project_briefs.extracted_summary, not to sessions.title.

The sessions landing page needs title populated or it shows "Untitled Session" for everything. Who writes it?

Fix: In the brief extraction Cloud Task (/api/tasks/brief-extraction), after writing extracted_summary, derive a title from extracted_summary.problem (first 60 chars) and UPDATE sessions SET title = $1.

🟠 Missing Timestamps — Ordering and Debugging Breaks
Every re-submittable entity needs a created_at. Currently missing:

Table	Impact
project_briefs	Can't determine latest brief on re-submission
hackathon_briefs	Same
pitch_recordings	Can't order multiple recordings; is_active alone isn't enough for audit
debriefs	Can't timestamp when each attempt was generated; can't show "Debrief from 2h ago"
coach_messages	Can't show message timestamps in the chat UI
Fix: Add created_at timestamptz DEFAULT now() to all five tables.

🟠 Undefined Enum Values — Runtime String Errors
The schema uses text columns for all status and role fields with no CHECK constraints or ENUMs. A typo in application code silently writes a bad value and the row is never fetched correctly.

Column	Valid Values (implied by spec, not enforced)
sessions.state	draft, brief_ready, pitch_recorded, qa_completed, debrief_ready, completed
project_briefs.status	pending, extracting, ready, failed, superseded
hackathon_briefs.status	same as above
pitch_recordings.status	pending, uploading, processing, ready, failed
qa_sessions.status	active, ended, abandoned
debriefs.status	generating, complete, failed
coach_messages.role	founder, coach
qa_turns.speaker	founder, vc, domain_expert, user_advocate
Fix: Either add CHECK (state IN (...)) constraints or use Postgres ENUMs. At minimum, sessions.state should have a CHECK since the entire navigation logic depends on it being a valid value.

🟡 Schema Inconsistencies — Maintenance Friction
7. debriefs mixes scalar columns with JSONB inconsistently

verdict and next_drill are scalar text columns, while the rest of DebriefOutput is JSONB. The DebriefOutput is a single struct generated atomically by the agent. Having some fields as columns and others as JSONB means:

The write path must split one object into 7 separate assignments
Adding a new field to DebriefOutput requires a schema migration for scalar fields but not for JSONB fields
Fix: Either store all of DebriefOutput as a single output jsonb NOT NULL column (simplest), or be consistent — make verdict and next_drill part of a top-level output jsonb field, and keep the individual columns only if they're queried directly.

8. raw_guidelines vs raw_context — inconsistent naming

project_briefs.raw_context and hackathon_briefs.raw_guidelines represent the same thing: raw textarea input from the founder. Inconsistent names make the codebase harder to navigate.

Fix: Rename hackathon_briefs.raw_guidelines → raw_context.

9. sessions.last_active_at has no defined update trigger

This column exists but no spec, API route, or hook documents when it's updated. The Q&A heartbeat updates qa_sessions.last_heartbeat_at. Should last_active_at be updated on every API call? Only on state transitions? A Postgres trigger on sessions.updated_at would cover it, but it's undefined.

10. qa_sessions missing FK to pitch_recordings

The system prompt injected into Gemini Live includes the pitch transcript. The transcript is fetched from pitch_recordings at Q&A start time. But qa_sessions has no record of which pitch was used. If a founder re-records after Q&A (edge case), there's no audit trail showing which transcript the judges actually heard.

Fix:

